Source: thinkutils
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Viet Anh Nguyen <vietanh.dev@gmail.com>
# Launchpad builders have NO network access. Every crate is vendored into the
# .orig tarball by scripts/build-ppa-source.sh and the build runs with
# CARGO_NET_OFFLINE=true, so Build-Depends lists only the toolchain and native
# libraries -- never librust-* packages.
#
# npm is deliberately absent, and that is not an oversight. tauri.conf.json has
# no beforeBuildCommand and frontendDist points at a directory of static files,
# so there is no frontend build step and no node_modules to vendor. That is the
# single reason this package is tractable on a network-less builder.
#
# @RUST_BUILD_DEPS@ is substituted per series by build-ppa-source.sh:
#   noble              -> rustc-1.83, cargo-1.83
#                         (the default rustc there is 1.75, too old to even
#                          parse a v4 Cargo.lock)
#   resolute, stonking -> rustc, cargo
Build-Depends:
 debhelper-compat (= 13),
@RUST_BUILD_DEPS@
 pkg-config,
 libwebkit2gtk-4.1-dev,
 libgtk-3-dev,
 libayatana-appindicator3-dev,
 librsvg2-dev,
 libssl-dev,
Standards-Version: 4.6.2
Homepage: https://github.com/vietanhdev/ThinkUtils
Vcs-Git: https://github.com/vietanhdev/ThinkUtils.git
Rules-Requires-Root: no

Package: thinkutils
# `any`, not a list. This is the one channel that is multi-arch without naming
# an architecture: Launchpad builds whatever the series has enabled, so the
# mechanism is what matters and narrowing this to `amd64` would silently stop
# producing arm64 builds with nothing else in the repo changing.
#
# Fan control needs thinkpad_acpi, which is x86-only; battery thresholds, the
# CPU governor and the system monitor are architecture neutral and work on an
# aarch64 ThinkPad such as the X13s.
Architecture: any
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}, policykit-1 | polkit
Recommends: lm-sensors
Suggests: clamav
Description: ThinkPad fan control, battery care and system monitoring
 ThinkUtils is a desktop utility for Lenovo ThinkPad laptops running Linux.
 It provides manual and temperature-curve fan control via thinkpad_acpi,
 battery charge threshold management, CPU governor and turbo-boost control,
 and live system monitoring.
 .
 Privileged operations go through a dedicated, package-owned helper authorised
 by a narrow polkit rule; the application itself runs unprivileged.
 .
 Fan control additionally requires the thinkpad_acpi module to be loaded with
 fan_control=1, which the application detects and can configure.
